getInitialLimit

public Integer getInitialLimit()

setInitialLimit

public void setInitialLimit(int initialLimit)
Parameters:
initialLimit - the initialLimit to set Sets how many connections are created in the cache when it is created or reinitialized. When this property is set to an integer value greater than 0, creating or reinitializing the cache automatically creates the specified number of connections, filling the cache in advance of need. Default: 0

getMaxLimit

public Integer getMaxLimit()

setMaxLimit

public void setMaxLimit(int maxLimit)
Parameters:
maxLimit - the maxLimit to set * Sets the maximum number of connection instances the cache can hold. The default value is Integer.MAX_VALUE, meaning that there is no limit enforced by the connection cache, so that the number of connections is limited only by the number of database sessions configured for the database.
